---
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import '../../styles/main.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Written Content - Chapter 1 | Hacker1 v1.0</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Chapter 1: The Word - Foundation principles of written content and sacred text integration." />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}favicon.svg`} />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Century+Schoolbook&family=Roboto:wght@400;500&family=EB+Garamond:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>
  <body class="dark-mode written-background">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb">
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}`}>Home</a> → 
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work`}>Finished Work</a> → 
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work/written`}>Written</a> → 
        Chapter 1
      </nav>
      
      <h1>Written Content - Chapter 1: The Word</h1>
      
      <div class="content-section implementation-background">
        <h2>Foundation of Written Expression</h2>
        <p>
          "In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God." - John 1:1
        </p>
        <p>
          Every piece of written content in our collection begins with this fundamental truth: 
          words have power, purpose, and eternal significance. Whether we're presenting 
          scripture, classical literature, or theological reflection, each word is chosen 
          with intention and reverence.
        </p>
        
        <blockquote class="highlight">
          "Your word is a lamp for my feet, a light on my path." - Psalm 119:105
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section solution-background">
        <h2>Scripture Integration</h2>
        <p>
          Our written works begin with scripture as the cornerstone. Like C.S. Lewis weaving 
          Christian allegory through Narnia, we integrate biblical truth throughout our content, 
          allowing divine wisdom to illuminate technical concepts and creative expression.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Core Principles:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Scripture as primary source of truth</li>
          <li>Classical literature as secondary wisdom</li>
          <li>Technical documentation with spiritual grounding</li>
          <li>Accessibility in both language and spirit</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Featured Scripture Collection:</h3>
        <div class="scripture-collection">
          <div class="scripture-item">
            <h4>"Trust in the Lord"</h4>
            <p>
              "Trust in the Lord with all your heart and lean not on your own understanding; 
              in all your ways submit to him, and he will make your paths straight." 
            </p>
            <cite>— Proverbs 3:5-6</cite>
          </div>
          
          <div class="scripture-item">
            <h4>"Work with Excellence"</h4>
            <p>
              "Whatever you do, work at it with all your heart, as working for the Lord, 
              not for human masters."
            </p>
            <cite>— Colossians 3:23</cite>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-section experimental-background">
        <h2>Classical Literature Integration</h2>
        <p>
          Following the pattern established by great Christian writers like John Milton, 
          George MacDonald, and Dorothy Sayers, we draw from the wealth of classical 
          literature to illustrate timeless truths and universal human experiences.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Featured Classical Excerpts:</h3>
        <div class="literature-collection">
          <div class="literature-item">
            <h4>Paradise Lost - Milton</h4>
            <p>
              "The mind is its own place, and in itself can make a heaven of hell, 
              a hell of heaven."
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="literature-item">
            <h4>Hamlet - Shakespeare</h4>
            <p>
              "To be, or not to be, that is the question: Whether 'tis nobler in the mind 
              to suffer the slings and arrows of outrageous fortune..."
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="navigation-section">
        <div class="nav-buttons">
          <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work/written`} class="button is-light">← Back to Written Works</a>
          <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}finished-work/graphic-ch1`} class="button is-primary">Next: Graphic Chapter 1 →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Add the custom floating bottom navbar -->
    <Navbar />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: white;
  }

  h1 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #8b7355;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: #f0f0f0;
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #8b7355;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .content-section h3 {
    color: #d4af37;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .content-section h4 {
    color: #e8d5b7;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .highlight {
    background: rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.1);
    border-left: 4px solid #d4af37;
    padding: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .scripture-collection, .literature-collection {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .scripture-item, .literature-item {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid #8b7355;
  }

  cite {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    opacity: 0.8;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .navigation-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }

  .nav-buttons {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .button {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .button.is-light {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    color: #f0f0f0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .button.is-light:hover {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .button.is-primary {
    background: #8b7355;
    color: white;
    border: 1px solid #8b7355;
  }

  .button.is-primary:hover {
    background: #a0845f;
  }

  /* Add padding to body to prevent navbar overlap */
  body {
    padding-bottom: 100px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .nav-buttons {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
    
    .container {
      padding: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
